:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Benachi\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3528:\"<p>Hello everyone. The meeting notes are from the themes team discussion on October 11, 2022. The themes team meets <strong>second</strong> and <strong>fourth</strong> Tuesday of every month at <a href=\"https://dateful.com/time-zone-converter\">15:00 UTC</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This week’s meeting agendas can be found <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2022/10/10/themes-team-meeting-agenda-for-october-11-2022/\">here</a>. You can read the <a href=\"https://wordpress.slack.com/archives/C02RP4Y3K/p1665500624380629\">full transcript </a>on our <a href=\"https://app.slack.com/client/T024MFP4J/C02RP4Y3K\">#themereview</a> channel. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Meeting facilitator: <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kafleg/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kafleg</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Note taker: @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/utz119/\">Benachi</a></li>\n</ul><h2><strong>1. Weekly updates</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The themes team published weekly updates about tickets and HelpScout emails. Here is the theme statistic for the past 7 days. The most current stats can be found <a href=\"https://themes.trac.wordpress.org/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>412 </strong>tickets were opened</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>428 </strong>tickets were closed:\n<ul><li><strong>418 </strong>tickets were made live.\n<ul><li><strong>39 </strong>new Themes were made live.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>379 </strong>Theme updates were made live.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>0</strong> more was approved but is waiting to be made live.</li>\n</ul></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>10</strong> tickets were not-approved.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>0</strong> ticket was closed-newer-version-uploaded.</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul><p>Number of reviewers: 2</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Block Themes Stats </strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>6</strong> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/tags/full-site-editing/\" target=\"_blank\">block themes</a> went live in the past 7 days.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Total 157 block themes in the repository. </li>\n</ul><h2>2. Update URI theme header in WordPress 6.1</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress 6.1 introduces a new <code>Update URI</code> <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/basics/main-stylesheet-style-css/\">theme header field</a>. This update will prevent naming conflicts with third-party themes when updating. <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2022/10/06/introducing-update-uri-theme-header-in-wordpress-6-1/\">More detail</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>3. index.php file is optional in Block themes</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With WordPress 6.1, index.php is now optional for the Block themes. The theme check plugin has been updated to reflect the change.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>4. Open Floor</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>No questions or comments related to the theme review were brought up during the open floor. </p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you, <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/latracal/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>latracal</a> <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/uxl/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>uxl</a> <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/robinwpdeveloper/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>robinwpdeveloper</a> for participating.</p>\n<p class=\"o2-appended-tags\"><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/meeting-notes/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>meeting-notes</a>, <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/themes-team/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>themes-team</a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0